Two main Programmmng Paradigm

1. Procedural Progarmming
2. OOPS

Why OOPs ?
In procedural programming paradigm free flow data control was not possible ...

What is OOPS?
It is a methodlogy or Paradigm to design a program using classes and objects...

Why OOPs ?

1. Data Abstraction
2. Data Encapsulation
3. Inheritance
4. Polymorphism

Data Abstraction : chhipa dena --- what is essential is made visible , actual core or engineering is made hideen 
Data Encapsulation : 




Class : Blueprint of a object / class in user defined data type
It is a user-defined data type, which holds its own data members and member functions, which can be accessed and used by creating an instance of that class. A class is like a blueprint for an object. 



Object
An Object is an identifiable entity with some characteristics and behavior.
objects are variable of type class...
An Object is an instance of a Class. When a class is defined, no memory is allocated but when it is instantiated (i.e. an object is created) memory is allocated.
